Dia. 2 If White Plays Elsewhere...
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par What happens if White plays elsewhere after Black \'a1\'e3?
\par
\par Black 1 is the vital point.
\par If White takes it at 1, Black plays dansu at B and lives because White can't play illegal move.
\par
\par That's why White played at 1 in the previous diagram.
\par }
